A real estate company, Lifecard Investment Company has launched Lifecard Co-Invest, a platform set to provide investment, development opportunities, information, tools, and funding for young, aspiring real estate investors.   Expert decries dwindling state of external reserves     Winners emerge in Union Bank, Mobo game competition     Fed Govt approves N3bn Sukuk fund for Numan-Jalingo road   Announcing this development at a news conference in Lagos, the Executive Director of Lifecard Investment Company, Grace Ofure Ibhakhomu, recalled that Co-investment was what empowered her a young lady when she set up shop as a real estate agent. “It gave me the knowledge of how my retirement and earnings will look like in a foreseeable future and today I am glad to say it gave me even more than I bargained for.” Also Developer, Lifecard Investment Limited, Udeze Somto Great urged young investors to tap into the opportunities which the platform has to offer many and still counting.